2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The use of thick materials in origami design may have applications in multimedia, such as creating 3D models or sculptures. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The ability to fold flat crease patterns with thick materials may have applications in computer vision and pattern recognition, such as in the development of new algorithms for object recognition. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The use of self-assembling systems in engineering innovation, as mentioned in the grant title, may have applications in robotics. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) - While less likely, the use of thick materials in origami design may also have applications in sound, such as in the creation of new musical instruments.
